Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 107
Edition:
Quote:  <i>steal the show</i> unexpected star of the show, often ahead of better known performers; first recorded, says Partridge, by <i>New Zealand Freelance</i> of 24 August 1934, of British batsmen to an Australian bowler in cricket match: `It seems we've stolen the show, Aussie.' NZA and elsewhere.
